Jun 15"}],"NEWS":[{"cat":"tournament","h":"Tunisia sack coach Lamouchi just one game into the World Cup","s":"Hours after a 5-1 thrashing by Sweden in their Group F opener, Tunisia's federation dismissed Sabri Lamouchi, making him the first coach fired while the 2026 tournament is still in progress. Veteran Herve Renard was lined up to step in ahead of the must-win clash with Japan.","src":"ESPN / Fox Sports / World Soccer Talk / Africa Top Sports"},{"cat":"tournament","h":"Extreme heat and severe storms keep disrupting host cities","s":"AccuWeather logged RealFeel temperatures topping 100F around Foxborough for Scotland-Morocco, while NWS 'lethal heat' alerts hit California, Oregon and Washington with forecasts near 110F. High winds also forced Boston's Fan Festival at City Hall Plaza to delay its opening after a storm-related closure.","src":"AccuWeather / Newsweek / NBC News"},{"cat":"tournament","h":"FIFA quietly slashes ticket prices across all 104 matches","s":"After a global backlash over dynamic pricing that pushed final seats past $5,000, FIFA cut prices tournament-wide and opened a $60 loyal-fan tier for every game - though only a few hundred per match. Reports say FIFA also returned roughly 70% of its block-booked hotel rooms amid soft demand.","src":"ESPN / AOL / PBS / The Conversation"},{"cat":"tournament","h":"Hydration-break boos unite players, fans and coaches against FIFA","s":"The mandatory three-minute pauses 22 minutes into each half have become a flashpoint: crowds have booed them even inside cooled stadiums, and a weather expert noted few matches actually met the heat threshold. Critics see a commercial play - Fox sells ad inventory in the breaks while Telemundo refuses to.","src":"ESPN / Al Jazeera / Yahoo Sports"},{"cat":"tournament","h":"Cape Verde's 40-year-old keeper Vozinha becomes the breakout story","s":"After making seven saves to hold favourites Spain to a 0-0 draw in Atlanta on debut, Cape Verde goalkeeper Vozinha turned into an overnight phenomenon, his Instagram following swelling by several million within a day as the human story of the group stage.","src":"ESPN / Al Jazeera / AP / NBC"}],"TOURN":[{"ic":"🏆","nm":"FIFA World Cup 2026","sub":"USA · Canada · Mexico","desc":"Group stage live. 48 teams, first match Jun 11.","status":"LIVE","cls":"b-tournament"},{"ic":"🏟️","nm":"UEFA Champions League","sub":"Europe · club","desc":"2025–26 concluded in late May. New league phase returns September 2026.","status":"OFF-SEASON","cls":"b-sched"},{"flag":"Spain","nm":"La Liga","sub":"Spain · domestic","desc":"2025–26 wrapped up in May. 2026–27 kicks off in August.","status":"OFF-SEASON","cls":"b-sched"},{"flag":"Australia","nm":"A-League Men","sub":"Australia · domestic","desc":"Off-season. 2025–26 finished; new season later in 2026.","status":"OFF-SEASON","cls":"b-sched"}],"FIFA":[{"ic":"📋","nm":"Biggest World Cup yet","sub":"Format","desc":"48 teams in 12 groups; top two plus 8 best third-placed sides reach the new Round of 32.","src":"FIFA / CBS"},{"ic":"🏟️","nm":"Club World Cup expanded","sub":"Club football","desc":"FIFA's 32-team Club World Cup ran Jun–Jul 2025 in the USA, now a permanent fixture despite player-welfare pushback.","src":"Sky / CBS"}],"MARQUEE":[{"day":"Sat · Jun 20","grp":"Group F","h":"Netherlands","a":"Sweden","et":"3:00 PM","std":"NRG Stadium","city":"Houston, USA"},{"day":"Sat · Jun 20","grp":"Group E","h":"Germany","a":"Ivory Coast","et":"6:00 PM","std":"Mercedes-Benz Stadium","city":"Atlanta, USA"},{"day":"Sun · Jun 21","grp":"Group H","h":"Spain","a":"Saudi Arabia","et":"6:00 PM","std":"AT&T Stadium","city":"Arlington, USA"},{"day":"Mon · Jun 22","grp":"Group J","h":"Argentina","a":"Austria","et":"9:00 PM","std":"SoFi Stadium","city":"Inglewood, USA"},{"day":"Tue · Jun 23","grp":"Group L","h":"England","a":"Ghana","et":"9:00 PM","std":"Mercedes-Benz Stadium","city":"Atlanta, USA"}],"WEEK":[{"d":"Friday, June 19","m":[["3:00 PM","USA","Australia","Seattle"],["6:00 PM","Scotla